<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>BFI response to the Culture, Media and Sport Committee</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Georgia; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by the British Film Institute [FBB0071]</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Executive summary</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 13.25pt; padding-left:8.05pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The BFI welcomes the opportunity to respond to the Culture, Media and Sport Committee Consultation on The Future of the BBC. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 13.25pt; padding-left:8.05pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In this response, we have confined ourselves – in line with a route suggested by the terms of reference for the Inquiry – to a general statement about the importance of the BBC as a public service broadcaster. The BFI will start to develop more detailed views on the future of the BBC once the timetable for Charter Review, the process by which it will be conducted and the specific policy options under consideration are set out by Government. We would welcome the opportunity to present oral evidence to the Committee’s Inquiry in due course, informed by our internal discussions and wider public debate, and would also be interested in submitting further written evidence. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 13.25pt; padding-left:8.05pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The BFI believes that public service broadcasting plays a crucial role in helping to underpin a flourishing culture and a vibrant creative economy in the UK. A strong BBC is at the heart of this. We want to see a secure, well-funded BBC which is able to maintain this position of strength throughout the next Charter period to the benefit of audiences and creators - for television, film, and online - and the creative economy. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 13.25pt; padding-left:8.05pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">For the BFI, the BBC, informed by its current public purposes, plays a vital role in serving audiences, including for film, and the creative economy in a number of different areas. In this submission we describe some of these areas which include production, archive and education and learning. A key outcome of Charter Review should be that these areas of activity continue to be strongly supported. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 13.25pt; padding-left:8.05pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We are seeking to build a strong, long-term strategic partnership between the BFI and the BBC as we clearly have complementary aims around both film and television. We have recently begun discussions with the BBC to put in place such a partnership which would deliver significant value to the public who fund both organisations. This partnership would also help to strengthen the relationship between film and the BBC as envisaged in Lord Smith’s Independent Review of Film Policy and the Government’s response to that Review.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span></li></ol></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">About the BFI</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 13.25pt; padding-left:8.05pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BFI is the lead organisation for film in the UK. Since 2011, it has combined a creative, cultural and industrial role as a Government arm’s length body and distributor of National Lottery funds. Its key priorities are to support a vibrant UK film culture by investing in film education, audience access, filmmaking and film heritage </span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 13.25pt; padding-left:8.05pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In October 2012, the BFI published </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">‘Film Forever, Supporting UK Film 2012-2017’,</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> which set out its strategy for the next five years, following an extensive industry consultation. It described the activities underpinning the BFI’s three strategic priorities:</span></li><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33.93pt; padding-left:8.62pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Expanding education and learning opportunities and boosting audience choice across the UK</span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 34.55pt; padding-left:8pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Supporting the future success of British film</span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 33.93pt; padding-left:8.62pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Unlocking film heritage for everyone in the UK to enjoy.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 34.55pt; padding-left:8pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">To that end, the BFI helps ensure that public policy supports film, television and the moving image and, in particular, British Film.</span></li></ol><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 13.25pt; padding-left:8.05pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Founded in 1933, the BFI is a registered charity governed by Royal Charter. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Response to questions</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 13.25pt; padding-left:8.05pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">At this stage, bearing in mind that it is over three years before a new BBC Charter will be put in </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">place,</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> we have chosen to focus in our submission on certain questions which form part of the Committee’s Terms of Reference. We will be having discussions at the BFI on other issues – such as funding mechanisms, governance and accountability – once the Government starts to lay out specific policy options around these matters.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:21.3pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The questions we have chosen to focus on at this stage are:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.36pt; padding-left:4.64pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">What should the BBC be for and what should be the purpose of public service broadcasting?</span></li></ul><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 7.5pt 14.7pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:-14.7pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.36pt; padding-left:4.64pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">How well has the BBC performed in the current Charter period in achieving its mission and public purposes?</span></li></ul><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.36pt; padding-left:4.64pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Are the public purposes in the current Charter the right ones? How might they change?</span></li></ul><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.7pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:-14.7pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.36pt; padding-left:4.64pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:0pt"><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">What role should the BBC play in developing technology and new ways of distributing content?</span></li></ul><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:8.05pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We set have grouped our answers to these questions below based on the BFI’s experience of working with the BBC over the period of the current Charter and bearing in mind our role as the lead body for film, the designated National Television Archive and an organisation which presents television programmes at the BFI Southbank and makes available research and publications around television.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">a)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Development and Production of British films</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The BBC plays a vital role as an investor in the development and production of British independent films with a budget of £11m per annum. During the current Charter period, the BFI (and before that, the UK Film Council the previous Lottery distributor for film), has co-invested in a wide range of feature films with BBC Films including </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Fish Tank</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Alan Partridge: Alpha Papa</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Philomena</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Without such investment by the BBC, audiences in the UK and internationally  would suffer from a significant reduction in the range of British films on offer, and the independent production sector in the UK would be forced to contract damaging our creative economy and in particular the capabilities of our talent and skillsbase. We therefore want to see a strong and well-funded BBC Films as a key part of the BBC throughout the next Charter period.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Archive</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The BFI is designated as custodian of the National TV Archive under the 2003 Communications Act. The collection comprises approximately 900,000 TV programmes, mainly from the 1970s to the present. We maintain a close relationship with the BBC on archive matters. It includes a unique continuous record of BBC broadcast output spanning 23 years.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Public access is available through our research viewings service (a BBC Charter obligation, discharged by contracting with BFI). The BFI also includes BBC archive material in its Southbank programme, on digital platforms such as Screenonline and Mediatheques, and on DVD releases. Our </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Doctor </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Who</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> at 50 </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">series of events at BFI Southbank in 2013 is a prominent example of this.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BBC programmes based on BFI research have included </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Black and White in Colour</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">The Last Machine</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">The Lost World of Mitchell and Kenyon</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, Further programmes are being developed. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The BFI partnered the BBC (as well as the Open University and Teachers’ TV) in the Creative Archive experiment offering films for non-commercial repurposing. We also supplied material to The Space a pilot online initiative between the BBC and Arts Council England.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In the coming years, we want to build and strengthen this working with the BBC around archive. The BFI has proposed creating a Digital National TV Archive in partnership with the BBC—bringing BBC technology and BFI legal rights together to create an innovative new public service. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BBC R&amp;D Department has long worked with the BFI, and has a technology platform which records, stores and can make available television content. In 2012 we formed a collaboration agreement with BBC to test a platform for the Digital National TV Archive. A pilot service has been available in the BFI Reuben Library for eighteen months. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We are planning to build on this pilot to develop a shared service platform for the use of other national institutions with an interest in television, such as the British Library, and the wider educational community.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Such joint working between the BBC and public organisations like the BFI which share similar goals should form an important part of the BBC’s role during the next Charter period. It would help to optimise the value of the funding supplied by both the licence fee payer and the taxpayer, and help ensure that the BBC contributes to the broader culture of the UK and serves as an enabler for the wider creative economy.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">c)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Education and Learning</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The output of BBC services, ranging from </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Blue Planet </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">to the </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Today</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> programme, from </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Who Do You Think You Are</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">?</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">to</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Bitesize</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> plays a crucial role in supporting and enabling education and learning at every level and for people of all ages and from all walks of life. Since its creation in 1922, the BBC has been a powerful force for good in advancing understanding and knowledge.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 42.55pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We are keen to explore ways in which we can help to refresh the BBC’s strategy in this sphere as part of our broader partnership discussions. We want to see how our emerging education strategy, which includes the Lottery-funded initiative Film Nation UK, can contribute to advancing film, television and the moving image in line with the objectives set out in our Royal Charter. Film Nation UK, which is aimed at 5-19 year olds, </span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">seeks to safeguard and boost future film audiences through learning and appreciation of film and stimulate a new generation of filmmakers and film talent.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">d)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Promotion of the cultural value of film and television across all BBC services</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The BBC has a vital role to play in promoting film across a variety of services to the benefit of audiences and the film sector in the UK. At present, its radio output including regular shows such as The Film Programme and Kermode and Mayo’s Film Review, along with other one-off series’ such as the Autumn 2013 season devoted to film music provides a valuable service for audience by exploring the breadth of film culture. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">However, although the season on music included a three-part BBC 4 series, television coverage of film culture generally is much weaker than its radio counterpart. Much of the BBC’s online coverage, including journalistic output, tends to be focussed on mainstream US films rather than on helping audiences to discover and learn more about the full range  of British and international film. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">As part of our proposed partnership with the Corporation we are keen to help </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">develop a joint edit</span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">orial proposition which helps audiences discover a much more diverse range of films using the BBC’s services and also helps strengthen our indigenous film industry. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt"><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Furthermore we believe the BBC and the BFI share a joint interest in exploring and promoting the cultural and educational value of television, as well as film.</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> A joined up approach to ‘screen culture’ could yield clearer policies for its future social application.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 42.55pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">To begin with, we believe we could quickly put together a powerful proposition around film and television culture, utilising the strength of both our own BFI Player and the iPlayer Plus that would be attractive to us both and help to significantly broaden audience appreciation and choice.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 42.55pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Georgia; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Caecilia LT Std Light'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Georgia; font-size:10pt"> See Annex One</span><span style="font-family:Georgia; font-size:10pt"> [Not published]</span></p></body></html>